[2026-03-09T00:43:36Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012MZbfjHePicGzYWC4nnMb1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I've found the bug. Let me document my findings:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've successfully identified the **project page workflow view** UI component and pinpointed the exact bug where clicking on a step shows a filename but doesn't load the file contents.\n\n### Bug Location\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` and `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n### The Bug\n\nIn the **Step Drawer component** (lines 251-284 of project_detail.html), when a user clicks on a workflow step node in the DAG visualization:\n\n1. **The `openDrawer()` function** (line 251) displays the step metadata (name, type, results, config keys like \"prompt\", \"command\", \"script\") showing the **filename** in lines 263-264:\n```javascript\nbody += '<dt>' + k + '</dt><dd class=\"mono\">' + step.config[k] + '</dd>';\n```\n\n2. **The content fetch** (line 274) attempts to load the actual file contents:\n```javascript\nfetch('/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(projectLabel) + '/workflows/' + \n    encodeURIComponent(workflowName) + '/steps/' + encodeURIComponent(stepName) + '/content')\n```\n\n### The Root Cause\n\nThe backend handler **`handleAPIStepContent()`** in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1134-1199) has a **logic flaw** when trying to load file content:\n\n1. **For \"prompt\" files** (lines 1177-1182): It tries to read from `filepath.Join(dir, prompt)` where `prompt` is the config value. This should work if the path is correct.\n\n2. **For \"command\" fields** (lines 1184-1186): It returns the command string directly (not a file read) - this works fine.\n\n3. **For \"script\" fields** (lines 1188-1195): It tries to read as a file first with `os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, script))`, and if that fails, it falls back to returning the script string directly.\n\n4. **The problem**: If the path resolution fails at all steps, it returns a 404 \"no content available\" (line 1198).\n\n### Key Code Sections\n\n**Frontend (project_detail.html, lines 251-284):**\n- Displays step name in drawer header\n- Shows metadata including the config fields (which contain filenames)\n- Fetches content from `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n- The content placeholder is shown while loading, then replaced with the fetched content\n\n**Backend (handler.go, lines 1134-1199 - `handleAPIStepContent()`):**\n- Resolves the project directory\n- Finds the workflow definition\n- Locates the step in the workflow\n- Attempts to read referenced files based on step config\n- Returns plain text response with the file contents\n\n**UI Components:**\n- **Drawer component** (HTML lines 40-47): A fixed slide-out panel on the right side with header and scrollable body\n- **CSS styling** (style.css lines 491-548): Defines the drawer's appearance and animation\n\n### Related Files\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - The main template with the workflow DAG and step drawer UI\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Contains all HTTP handlers including `handleAPIStepContent()`\n3. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - CSS for the drawer and related components\n4. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base layout template\n5. `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Domain model for workflows (referenced by dsl.Parse)\n\nThe workflow visualization is an SVG DAG (lines 163-249 of project_detail.html) with clickable step nodes that trigger `openDrawer()` function, which then attempts to fetch and display step content via a REST API endpoint."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a07ba961a1c496e0b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51462\ntool_uses: 9\nduration_ms: 18813</usage>"}]}]},"pa