[2026-03-09T00:46:16Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XK3hbuGTHZXg3AMDcjoEiv","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have the information you need. Here's my analysis:\n\n## Findings\n\n### 1. **Is `file(\"...\")` syntax preserved in Step.Config?**\n\n**YES, it is preserved as-is.** The parser does NOT resolve or unwrap the `file(\"...\")` syntax during parsing.\n\nIn `parseValue()` (lines 298-342 of parser.go), when the parser encounters a function call like `file(\"...\")`:\n- It assembles the string piece by piece (lines 311-326)\n- Builds up: `file(\"path/to/file\")`\n- Returns this complete string to be stored in `step.Config[key]`\n\nThe parser simply stores the string exactly as it appears in the DSL. For example, if you write:\n```\nprompt = file(\"prompts/agent.md\")\n```\n\nIt gets stored as the literal string `\"file(\\\"prompts/agent.md\\\")\"` in the config map.\n\n### 2. **Step struct definition**\n\nLocated in `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` (lines 21-26):\n\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n\tName    string\n\tType    StepType\n\tResults []string\n\tConfig  map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `Config` is a simple `map[string]string` - all values are stored as plain strings\n- `Type` is inferred during parsing based on which key is present (`prompt` → StepTypeAgent, `run` → StepTypeScript, `workflow_name` → StepTypeWorkflow)\n- `Results` is a slice of declared result names\n- The step stores the raw, unprocessed config values\n\nThe actual resolution of `file(\"...\")` to file contents would happen **later**, when the step is executed (not during parsing)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae51954ceed6e2dbd (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 21495\ntool_uses: 4\nduration_ms: 7931</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ad63e92-d8fd-45c5-affb-b4d21a740cf7","uuid":"9a84ca5f-7592-467d-a1c7-d2e06c883185","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read the DSL parser at internal/dsl/ to understand how step config values (especially \"prompt = file(...)\") are stored. I need to know:\n1. Is the `file(\"...\")` syntax preserved in the step's Config map, or is it resolved/unwrapped during parsing?\n2. What does the Step struct look like in domain?\n\nLook at internal/dsl/parse.go and internal/domain/workflow.go (or wherever the Step type is defined).","agentId":"ae51954ceed6e2dbd","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have the information you need. Here's my analysis:\n\n## Findings\n\n### 1. **Is `file(\"...\")` syntax preserved in Step.Config?**\n\n**YES, it is preserved as-is.** The parser does NOT resolve or unwrap the `file(\"...\")` syntax during parsing.\n\nIn `parseValue()` (lines 298-342 of parser.go), when the parser encounters a function call like `file(\"...\")`:\n- It assembles the string piece by piece (lines 311-326)\n- Builds up: `file(\"path/to/file\")`\n- Returns this complete string to be stored in `step.Config[key]`\n\nThe parser simply stores the string exactly as it appears in the DSL. For example, if you write:\n```\nprompt = file(\"prompts/agent.md\")\n```\n\nIt gets stored as the literal string `\"file(\\\"prompts/agent.md\\\")\"` in the config map.\n\n### 2. **Step struct definition**\n\nLocated in `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` (lines 21-26):\n\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n\tName    string\n\tType    StepType\n\tResults []string\n\tConfig  map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `Config` is a simple `map[string]string` - all values are stored as plain strings\n- `Type` is inferred during parsing based on which key is present (`prompt` → StepTypeAgent, `run` → StepTypeScript, `workflow_name` → StepTypeWorkflow)\n- `Results` is a slice of declared result names\n- The step stores the raw, unprocessed config values\n\nThe actual resolution of `file(\"...\")` to file contents would happen **later**, when the step is executed (not during parsing)."}],"totalDurationMs":7931,"totalTokens":21495,"totalToolUseCount":4,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7474,"cache_read_input_tokens":13598,"output_tokens":416,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7474},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
[2026-03-09T00:46:16Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01X2L13iYjxtqADhXEwahJRY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of the code. Let me analyze the bug:\n\nLooking at `handleAPIStepContent` (handler.go:1134-1201), the logic is:\n1. Find the workflow and step\n2. If step has `prompt` config, call `extractFilePath(prompt)` and read the file\n3. If step has `run` config, return the command\n4. If step has `script` config, try to read file or return inline value\n\nThe `extractFilePath` function works correctly - it unwraps `file(\"...\")` syntax.\n\nThe test `TestAPIStepContent_PromptFile` (handler_test.go:805-834) passes, which means the backend API correctly returns file contents.\n\n\nSo the bug must be in the frontend JavaScript. Looking at the `openDrawer` function in the template, I can see it's fetching the step content and building the drawer display...\n\nBuilding the drawer content... I'm looking at the fetch call to load step content and tracing through the backend handler to see if it's actually retrieving the file data correctly. The frontend is set up to display the content in a pre-formatted block, but I need to verify the API endpoint is properly extracting and returning the file contents from the step configuration. I'm realizing the empty string case would just show \"No content available\" as expected for errors, which is fine. But I should actually look at what's already been changed in this codebase—the handler and test files are modified, and so is the HTML template, so someone's already been working on this. Let me check the git diff to see what changes have been made so far.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":13248,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1852,"cache_read_input_tokens":53988,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1852},"output_tokens":8,"servi